    question: "How does the AI handle roofing enquiries — especially storm damage?",
    answer: "Storm damage calls are treated as emergencies. When a caller describes tiles blown off, a leak coming through the ceiling, lead flashing lifted, or structural damage after high winds, the AI captures the extent of the damage, whether the property is currently leaking, and whether anyone is at risk. It escalates storm damage calls immediately because you know as well as we do — after a storm, you get more calls in 24 hours than you normally get in a month. Missing even one of them is money left on the table."
